


ZFORCE(1)                                               ZFORCE(1)


NNAAMMEE
       zforce - force a '.gz' extension on all gzip files

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       zzffoorrccee [ name ...  ]

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       _z_f_o_r_c_e  forces  a  .gz extension on all _g_z_i_p files so that
       _g_z_i_p will not compress them twice.  This can be useful for
       files with names truncated after a file transfer.  On sys-
       tems with a 14 char limitation on file names, the original
       name  is  truncated  to  make room for the .gz suffix. For
       example, 12345678901234 is renamed  to  12345678901.gz.  A
       file name such as foo.tgz is left intact.

SSEEEE AALLSSOO
       gzip(1), znew(1), zmore(1), zgrep(1), zdiff(1), gzexe(1)








































